  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to investigate the effect of dual site-dual channel non-invasive
      brain stimulation for recovery of motor function in healthy subjects. Simultaneous dual
      site-dual channel stimulation was applied by using two sets of transcranial direct current
      stimulation devices. All subjects will go through four conditions of transcranial direct
      current stimulation with for 30 minutes. Four conditions are 1) Dual stimulation: i) anodal
      stimulation on right primary motor cortex and cathodal stimulation on left primary motor
      cortex, ii) anodal stimulation on right premotor cortex and cathodal stimulation on left
      supraorbital area. 2) M1 stimulation: anodal stimulation on right primary motor cortex and
      cathodal stimulation on left primary motor cortex; 3) PMC stimulation: anodal stimulation on
      right premotor cortex and cathodal stimulation on left supraorbital area. 4) sham stimulation
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
